title.narrative: By 2020, disadvantaged children, adolescents and families have improved their knowledge and attitudes on key behaviour and social norms/practices on integrated sector priorities

description.narrative: Families, adolescents and children were reached with key-messages and engaged to adopt essential family practices such as on Infant and Young Children Feeding, hygiene practices, HIV prevention, birth registration, school retention, ending child marriage, prevention of violence against children, immunization, prevention of malaria through multiple strategies using a mix of mass-media, mid-media, social mobilization and interpersonal communication. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:14/01/2020
